National Security Adviser Susan E. Rice has announced that Philip Gordon, Special Assistant to the President and White House Coordinator for the Middle East, North Africa, and the Gulf Region, will be stepping down. He will be succeeded by Rob Malley, currently the NSC Senior Director for Iran, Iraq, Syria, and the Gulf States. Malley will assume his new position on April 6, 2015. Rice thanked Gordon for his service and expressed confidence in Malley's ability to provide a seamless transition. Malley is a respected expert on the Middle East and has been involved in shaping the country's policy on Iran, Iraq, Syria, and the Gulf since February 2014.